The course is a practical training of translating professional texts from the foreign language into Estonian and vice versa.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the skills of translating LSP-texts on business from the foreign language into Estonian and vice versa. During the seminars, students acquire the principles of preparatory analysis of texts and learn different translation strategies and methods for achieving the aim of the translation task. Students enhance their command of business terminology in Estonian as well as in the foreign language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course you have acquired the skills of  - analysis of LSP-texts on business in Estonian and in the foreign language and translating these texts, - using the appropriate terminology, - choosing the appropriate translation strategy for carrying out the translation task, - finding the necessary information for translation, assessing it and using the appropriate sources as well as justifying your translation choices, - applying the necessary digital competences, - solving translation problems individually and as a member of a team, managing your time accordingly.
